Cozy up this winter with a hot cup of dairy free hot chocolate ❄️⛄️ Our allergy friendly cocoa mix is easy to make and uses pantry staples, plus it makes a great gift for friends or family with food allergies! Get the recipe on our website, the link is in our bio 👈🏻 

#dairyfreerecipes #hotchocolatetime #glutenfreerecipes #hotcocoa

These homemade stained glass gingerbread ornaments are so fun to make! We like this with starlight mints, but you can use jolly ranchers as well. These are twice baked so they are very sturdy and you can keep these for a couple years as well if you spray a clear coat of paint on top and store in a container that will keep any moisture out. 

These are gluten free and allergy friendly as well, so our gingerbread dough is safe to handle if you have celiac disease or severe dairy or egg allergies! Get the full recipe and instructions on our website, link is in our bio 👈🏻 

#dairyfreeglutenfree #christmasdiy #homemadeornaments #christmasdecor #allergyfriendly

I don’t share a ton of savory recipes on our website, but we have quite a few good ones! If you haven't tried our tater tot casserole yet, get this scheduled on your menu. It's creamy, cheesy, and completely dairy free. 😍 It's a recipe that we make regularly and it's becoming a reader favorite as well. Get the recipe on our website, the link is in our profile!

#dairyfreerecipes #glutenfreerecipes #allergyfriendly #weeknightdinner

Get the template and recipe on our website, the link is in our bio 👈🏻 

#gingerbreadhouses #glutenfree #dairyfree #allergyfriendly #peanutfree

We have a new recipe today: soursop (aka guanabana) lemonade! 😍 This is good if you love tropical flavors and I think it’s my new favorite drink for this spring and summer. 

If you haven’t tried soursop yet, add it to your list of things to try, it’s incredible! We can’t get fresh soursop here, but our local Walmart has the Nilo 100% soursop juice and it’s so good in lemonade. We have other recipes coming your way using this juice!

Get the recipe link in our profile 🍋 

#lemonade #soursop #guanabana #allergyfriendly #homemadelemonade

One of my favorite things about late summer is the abundance of fresh produce this time of year! 🍑✨🥬 You can make the best salads with seasonal produce and @localbounti greens that are grown indoors and are in-season all year around! 🌞 

Check out this easy and amazing end-of-summer salad that’s dairy free, too! Perfect for a light snack or a side salad. Use as much or as little of each ingredient you’d like:

@localbounti Crispy Green Leaf lettuce
Fresh blackberries
Fresh peaches
Cucumbers
Dairy free feta cheese (I used Violife)
Natural nitrate-free bacon crumbles 
Fresh ground black pepper

Drizzle with olive oil mixed with high quality balsamic vinegar.
Add everything to a bowl and keep it all separate (like we did in the video), or chop it and toss it all together in a bowl! Enjoy! 💚 

#dairyfreerecipes #dairyfree #dairyfreeglutenfree #glutenfree #glutenfreerecipes

Product and food photographers, this tip is just for you: you can use a high quality polarizing filter to help reduce glare on shiny objects! This works great with products that have shiny packaging, glassware, drinks, etc. This @urth CPL polarizing lens filter helps to add some control over reflections that can happen even with diffused light. This helps reduce the glare a bit without eliminating it completely so we can show off what’s inside the packaging or glass. The light source and direction didn’t change between the before and after comparisons. 

The Urth Magnetic Essentials Filter Kit system make it so easy to pop filters on quickly and stack multiple filters, I can’t wait use these for my landscape and waterfall photography next! I love that the CPL polarizing filter adds some warmth but does not add a weird brown color to my photos like some other ones I’ve used. 

Thank you Urth for sponsoring this post 📸

#productphotography #foodphotography #drinkphotography #foodphotographyandstyling #canonphotographers #foodphotographytips

Our gluten free and dairy free version of the viral baked feta pasta makes an easy and fuss-free weeknight meal! You can leave this recipe as-is for a vegan version, or you can add chicken sausage for a complete dinner with added protein.

I had originally wanted to post this a couple years ago but didn’t end up doing it and I decided to finally post it since I love this recipe and it’s easy. Better late than never, right? 😉

This recipe is adapted from the original recipe by Jenni at @liemessa blog and made popular in America by MacKenzie at Grilled Cheese Social and Yumna at Feel Good Foodie. 

I tested this recipe with 3 different kinds of dairy free feta cheese: Violife, Daiya, and Good Planet. The best one for this recipe is the Daiya feta cheese! I love Violife but it melts too much when cooked. 

You can get the printable recipe on our website, check our profile for the link!
